From 7c9e7ba6b2649b3f2b0eb2e6042eacb336bf8ff2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ren Wang <iamwrm@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 21:55:44 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] Route chatgpt_oauth models through the OpenAI credential
 + Codex request shape

Adds AuthScheme::ChatgptOauth as a per-model credential source:

- xai-grok-sampler: new AuthScheme variant (wire format = Bearer); when
  set, serialized Responses requests are rewritten for the ChatGPT Codex
  backend (system input items hoisted into `instructions`, store:false
  forced, reasoning.summary=auto, max_output_tokens/temperature/top_p
  stripped).
- xai-grok-shell: resolve_credentials sources the bearer from the stored
  OpenAI credential (never falls back to the xAI session token or
  XAI_API_KEY), models with the scheme always count as BYOK for the
  session-token auth gate, and both the aux-model and session sampler
  configs install OpenAiCodexBearerResolver (live refresh) plus the
  ChatGPT backend headers (chatgpt-account-id, originator, OpenAI-Beta).
- [model.*] config accepts auth_scheme = "chatgpt_oauth".
